## Decisions Made
- Deferred execution model: Register items as tasks during classification, batch-execute after all decisions — rationale: user sees full picture before any code changes, maximizes parallel execution efficiency
- Task status mapping: Skipped items marked as `completed` (with skip annotation), failed items marked as `completed` (with failure details) — rationale: task system only has pending/in_progress/completed/deleted, `completed` is closest fit
- Phase 2/3 boundary: Full AMBIGUOUS analysis presented in Phase 2 (Report), Phase 3 only handles user decisions — rationale: user sees everything at once, then decides

## Problems Encountered
- "Stopping on Single Failure" common mistake referenced old workflow behavior (move failed OBVIOUS to AMBIGUOUS) — resolved by updating to match new batch execution model
- SKILL.md Phase 3 said "Present AMBIGUOUS items" duplicating Phase 2 — resolved by changing to "Resolve AMBIGUOUS items (already presented in Phase 2)"
- Edge case: zero approved tasks after all skips not handled in Phase 4 — resolved by adding guard clause to skip to Phase 5

## Constraints Identified
- Task system limited to pending/in_progress/completed/deleted statuses — no native "skipped" or "failed" status, requires annotation in description
- Files grouped per subagent: tasks touching the same file must be sequential within one subagent to avoid edit conflicts

